<doc id="452330" wikidata="Q243107" url="?curid=452330" title="Cerdon, Ain">
<text>Cerdon () is a commune in the Ain department in eastern France.

It is known for its pink sparkling wine, and for its copper factory, the only one of its kind in France. The &#x27;Cuivrerie&#x27; (copper factory) closed in 2010.

